  "texts": [
    "11When computing the in-in expectation value Exp k, we need to add to the scattering amplitude the contribution from the Cut 1 ′ 2 ′ term in (4.61).",
    "In fact, out of the one-loop diagrams shown in figure 8, only the D topology admits a non-zero cut in this channel.",
    "This was previously exemplified in sections 3.2 and 4.6.",
    "Thus, for the A, B and C topologies, there is actually no difference between the time-ordered amplitude iM and Exp k. The only term to add is the cut of D obtained by taking the discontinuity of two propagators and including appropriate signs as determined by the rules (4.47):Cut G D a 1,a 2,a 3,a 4,a 5 = 4π 2 e ϵγ E d D ℓ iπ D/2 1 (ℓ 2 +iε) a 1 ((ℓ+q 1) 2 -iε) a 3 ((ℓ-q 2) 2 -iε) a 4(5.4)×δ [a 2] + (ℓ-p 1 + 1 2 q 1) 2 +m 2 1 δ [a 5] + (ℓ+p 2 -1 2 q 2) 2 +m 2 2,where we introduced the shorthand notationδ [a] ≡ (-1) a-1 (a -1)!",
    "δ (a-1) (x)."
  ],
